Join the Conversation To find out more about Facebook commenting please read the Conversation Guidelines and FAQs UI roundup: Hawkeye volleyball, field hockey fall on road 8:41 p.m. CDT October 2, 2015 Iowa athletics 
The Iowa volleyball team lost to Ohio State 3-1 Friday night in Columbus, Ohio. The Hawkeyes fell 22-25, 19-25, 25-18, 11-25. 
Iowa (10-6, 0-3 Big Ten) was paced by Mikaela Gunderson, who had 10 kills and three blocks against the No. 13 Buckeyes (13-2, 2-1). 
Ashley Mariani added nine kills. Loxley Keala posted 35 assists. Annika Olsen had 20 digs. Lauren Brobst and Regan Davey both recorded six kills. 
â€¢ FIELD HOCKEY: Iowa lost to Northwestern 4-0 at Lakeside Field in Evanston, Ill. 
The Hawkeyes (7-5, 1-2 Big Ten) allowed four unanswered goals to Northwestern (9-4, 2-2) on the day. Iowa trailed 1-0 at halftime. Read or Share this story: http://icp-c.com/1L9yqsK TOP VIDEOS
